tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Finished T93 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Won the U.S. Kids World Junior Championship at 9 years old with his dad caddying...Tied for fifth place during stroke play at the 2013 U.S. Amateur Public Links Championship...Fell to Justin Shin in 19 holes during the first round of match play...Tied for 13th at the 2013 Western Amateur Championship with rounds of 69, 69, 72 and 73 for a 283 total...Lost in the first round of match play to teammate Jordan Niebrugge, 4 and 3...Tied for 13th during the stroke play portion of the 2012 U.S. Amateur with rounds of 68 and 71...Tied for second during stroke play at the U.S. Amateur Public Links Championship with a 6-under total of 136 that featured rounds of 72 and 64, fell, 2 and 1, in the first round of match play to Sam Saunders...Named first-team All-Big 12 selection as a sophomore in 2012 at Oklahoma State...Best finish of the season was a runner-up performance at the Puerto Rico Classic and closed with rounds of 69 and 66 to come in with a 9-under 207 total...Named an honorable mention All-American by Golfweek as a junior in 2013 as well as a first-team All-Big 12 pick and a first-team Academic All-Big 12 selection...Tied for second place at the U.S. Collegiate Championship...Was runner-up at the Big 12 Championship with a 3-over 213 that included rounds of 70-69-74.
tourBios.personal: Uses a quarter from the 1960s as a ball marker...Wants to play St. Andrews...Father, Ron Gooch, spent five seasons in the minor league system of the Texas Rangers...Dream foursome would include his dad, Kelsey Cline and Steve Ball...Favorite pro sports team is the Dallas Cowboys...Twitter name is @TalorGooch.

tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Prevailed in a eight-player-for-four-spots playoff to claim a T15 finish at the Florida Qualifying Tournament...Finished T2 at the Syncrude Boreal Open after falling to Kevin Spooner in a five-hole playoff...Posted back-to-back top-10 finishes at The Wildfire Invitational (T6) and the Cape Breton Celtic Classic (T4) to finish the season 17th on the Order of Merit. Earned an exemption into the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament's second stage.
